{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883629467,"sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9ae04001xOU4g7afvN6cuV","messageID":"msg_d7ae9a1aa001R9CjofZaUQoZRr","sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-86c375abcbb043bd95702956d21e866e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/Dockerfile"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/Dockerfile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ============================================\n2: # Build Arguments\n3: # ============================================\n4: ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\n5: ARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\n6: ARG BUILD_VERSION=dev\n7: ARG BUILD_TIME\n8: ARG GIT_COMMIT\n9: \n10: # ============================================\n11: # Stage 1: Builder\n12: # ============================================\n13: FROM golang:${GO_VERSION}-alpine AS builder\n14: \n15: # Build metadata\n16: ARG BUILD_VERSION\n17: ARG BUILD_TIME\n18: ARG GIT_COMMIT\n19: \n20: # Install build tools\n21: RUN apk add --no-cache \\\n22:     python3 \\\n23:     py3-pip \\\n24:     gcc \\\n25:     musl-dev \\\n26:     git \\\n27:     ca-certificates\n28: \n29: # Set working directory\n30: WORKDIR /build\n31: \n32: # Go dependency optimization - download first for caching\n33: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n34: RUN go mod download\n35: \n36: # Copy Go source code\n37: COPY ./pkg ./pkg\n38: COPY ./cmd ./cmd\n39: \n40: # Build agentd with embedded version info\n41: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build \\\n42:     -ldflags=\"-s -w -X main.Version=${BUILD_VERSION} -X main.BuildTime=${BUILD_TIME} -X main.GitCommit=${GIT_COMMIT}\" \\\n43:     -o agentd \\\n44:     ./cmd/agentd\n45: \n46: # Copy Python source and dependencies\n47: COPY ./cmd/picod /build/picod\n48: COPY requirements.txt ./\n49: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n50: \n51: # ============================================\n52: # Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)\n53: # ============================================\n54: FROM builder AS verifier\n55: \n56: # Run Go tests\n57: RUN go test ./... -v -coverprofile=coverage.out || echo \"Some tests may have failed\"\n58: \n59: # Generate test report\n60: RUN go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html || echo \"Coverage report generation skipped\"\n61: \n62: # Run Python tests if they exist\n63: RUN if [ -d \"/build/picod/tests\" ]; then \\\n64:       pytest /build/picod/tests -v || echo \"Python tests may have failed\"; \\\n65:     fi\n66: \n67: # ============================================\n68: # Stage 3: Runtime\n69: # ============================================\n70: FROM alpine:${ALPINE_VERSION} AS runtime\n71: \n72: # Build metadata\n73: ARG BUILD_VERSION\n74: ARG GIT_COMMIT\n75: \n76: # Labels for image metadata\n77: LABEL maintainer=\"agentcube@volcano.sh\" \\\n78:       version=\"${BUILD_VERSION}\" \\\n79:       git.commit=\"${GIT_COMMIT}\" \\\n80:       description=\"AgentCube Runtime Image\" \\\n81:       org.opencontainers.image.title=\"AgentCube\" \\\n82:       org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Runtime Image\" \\\n83:       org.opencontainers.image.version=\"${BUILD_VERSION}\" \\\n84:       org.opencontainers.image.source=\"https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\"\n85: \n86: # Install runtime dependencies only\n87: RUN apk add --no-cache \\\n88:     ca-certificates \\\n89:     python3 \\\n90:     py3-pip \\\n91:     tzdata \\\n92:     && update-ca-certificates \\\n93:     && rm -rf /var/cache/apk/*\n94: \n95: # Create non-privileged user\n96: RUN addgroup -g 1000 agentcube && \\\n97:     adduser -D -u 1000 -G agentcube agentcube\n98: \n99: # Set working directory\n100: WORKDIR /app\n101: \n102: # Copy compiled binaries from builder\n103: COPY --from=builder /build/agentd /app/agentd\n104: \n105: # Copy Python environment\n106: COPY --from=builder /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages\n107: COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod\n108: \n109: # Set ownership\n110: RUN chown -R agentcube:agentcube /app\n111: \n112: # Switch to non-privileged user\n113: USER agentcube\n114: \n115: # Expose ports\n116: EXPOSE 8080 9090\n117: \n118: # Health check\n119: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n120:     CMD agentd health || exit 1\n121: \n122: # Default environment variables\n123: ENV AGENTCUBE_ENV=production \\\n124:     AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL=info \\\n125:     AGENTCUBE_LOG_FORMAT=json \\\n126:     AGENTCUBE_PORT=8080 \\\n127:     AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED=true \\\n128:     AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT=9090\n129: \n130: # Entry point\n131: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/agentd\"]\n132: \n133: # Default command (can be overridden)\n134: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n\n(End of file - total 134 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ============================================\n# Build Arguments\n# ============================================\nARG GO_VERSION=1.21\nARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\nARG BUILD_VERSION=dev\nARG BUILD_TIME\nARG GIT_COMMIT\n\n# ============================================\n# Stage 1: Builder\n# ============================================\nFROM golang:${GO_VERSION}-alpine AS builder\n\n# Build metadata\nARG BUILD_VERSION\nARG BUILD_TIME\nARG GIT_COMMIT\n\n# Install build tools","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/Dockerfile","time":{"start":1775883629448,"end":1775883629465}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883629469,"sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9b0d1001vzBcg0hvyIyByW","messageID":"msg_d7ae9a1aa001R9CjofZaUQoZRr","sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-962e2d3ec8a849b3a8519c6f4989ec9a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-032\n5: - **Title**: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n6: - **Module**: docker\n7: - **Language**: Dockerfile\n8: - **Size**: S\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for Dockerfile multi-stage builds with 3 images in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for building AgentCube components using multi-stage Docker builds to optimize image size, build time, and security. The specification covers three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime stages, with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to ensure proper implementation of the multi-stage build pattern.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Multi-stage build structure with three stages\n18: \n19: The system SHALL implement Dockerfile multi-stage builds with three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Dockerfile defines three FROM statements\n22: - **GIVEN** a Dockerfile for an AgentCube component\n23: - **WHEN** the Dockerfile is examined\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL contain exactly three FROM statements\n25: - **AND** the first FROM SHALL define the builder stage\n26: - **AND** the second FROM SHALL define the dependency stage\n27: - **AND** the third FROM SHALL define the runtime stage\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Builder stage uses build tools\n30: - **GIVEN** the builder stage FROM statement\n31: - **WHEN** the builder stage is defined\n32: - **THEN** it SHALL use an image with build tools (e.g., golang:1.21, node:18, python:3.11)\n33: - **AND** it SHALL include necessary build dependencies\n34: - **AND** it SHALL be named with AS builder\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Dependency stage extracts runtime dependencies\n37: - **GIVEN** the dependency stage FROM statement\n38: - **WHEN** the dependency stage is defined\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL copy artifacts from the builder stage\n40: - **AND** it SHALL extract only runtime dependencies\n41: - **AND** it SHALL be named with AS dependencies\n42: - **AND** it SHALL use a minimal base image (e.g., debian:bookworm-slim, alpine:3.18)\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses minimal base image\n45: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage FROM statement\n46: - **WHEN** the runtime stage is defined\n47: - **THEN** it SHALL use a minimal base image (e.g., distroless, alpine, scratch)\n48: - **AND** it SHALL copy only necessary artifacts from dependency stage\n49: - **AND** it SHALL NOT include build tools or development dependencies\n50: - **AND** it SHALL be the final stage (no AS name required)\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: Build artifacts transfer between stages\n53: \n54: The system SHALL properly transfer build artifacts between the three stages using COPY --from.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: COPY --from builder to dependencies\n57: - **GIVEN** the dependency stage\n58: - **WHEN** copying artifacts from the builder stage\n59: - **THEN** COPY --from=builder SHALL be used\n60: - **AND** only compiled binaries or packaged artifacts SHALL be copied\n61: - **AND** build artifacts SHALL be copied to appropriate locations (e.g., /app, /usr/local/bin)\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: COPY --from dependencies to runtime\n64: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n65: - **WHEN** copying artifacts from the dependency stage\n66: - **THEN** COPY --from=dependencies SHALL be used\n67: - **AND** only runtime dependencies and executables SHALL be copied\n68: - **AND** source artifacts (e.g., source code, build cache) SHALL NOT be copied\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Dependency isolation in intermediate stage\n71: - **GIVEN** the dependency stage\n72: - **WHEN** processing dependencies\n73: - **THEN** the stage SHALL install and configure runtime dependencies\n74: - **AND** the stage SHALL NOT include source code\n75: - **AND** the stage SHALL prepare the final dependency structure for the runtime stage\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Layer optimization and caching\n78: \n79: The system SHALL optimize Docker layer usage and leverage build cache effectively.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Dockerfile instructions are ordered for caching\n82: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile structure\n83: - **WHEN** examining instruction order\n84: - **THEN** frequently changing instructions (e.g., COPY source code) SHALL appear later\n85: - **AND** stable instructions (e.g., RUN apt-get install) SHALL appear earlier\n86: - **AND** dependency installation SHALL be grouped into single RUN instructions\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: COPY of dependencies before source code\n89: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n90: - **WHEN** copying files\n91: - **THEN** dependency manifests (package.json, go.mod, requirements.txt) SHALL be copied first\n92: - **AND** dependency installation SHALL run before copying source code\n93: - **AND** source code SHALL be copied after dependencies are installed\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Multi-line RUN instructions are combined\n96: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n97: - **WHEN** multiple related commands are needed\n98: - **THEN** commands SHALL be combined using && or \\\n99: - **AND** package installation and cleanup SHALL be in single RUN layer\n100: - **AND** intermediate build artifacts SHALL be cleaned up in same layer\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: Image size optimization\n103: \n104: The system SHALL produce minimal final images through effective multi-stage build usage.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Runtime image excludes build tools\n107: - **GIVEN** the final runtime image\n108: - **WHEN** inspecting the image\n109: - **THEN** build tools (gcc, go, node, python-dev) SHALL NOT be present\n110: - **AND** development dependencies SHALL NOT be present\n111: - **AND** build cache files SHALL NOT be present\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Runtime image includes only necessary files\n114: - **GIVEN** the final runtime image\n115: - **WHEN** examining image contents\n116: - **THEN** only executable binaries SHALL be present\n117: - **AND** only runtime libraries SHALL be present\n118: - **AND** only configuration files SHALL be present\n119: - **AND** source code SHALL NOT be present\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Multi-stage reduces final image size\n122: - **GIVEN** comparison between single-stage and multi-stage builds\n123: - **WHEN** measuring final image sizes\n124: - **THEN** the multi-stage build SHALL produce a smaller image\n125: - **AND** the size reduction SHALL be significant (at least 50% smaller than single-stage)\n126: - **AND** the builder and dependency stages SHALL not be included in final image\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Security hardening in multi-stage builds\n129: \n130: The system SHALL implement security best practices through multi-stage build structure.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Runtime image uses distroless or minimal base\n133: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage base image\n134: - **WHEN** examining the base image\n135: - **THEN** the base image SHALL be distroless or minimal (e.g., alpine, scratch)\n136: - **AND** the base image SHALL NOT include package managers (apt, apk, yum)\n137: - **AND** the base image SHALL have minimal attack surface\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Non-root user configuration\n140: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n141: - **WHEN** configuring the container user\n142: - **THEN** a non-root user SHALL be created with USER instruction\n143: - **AND** the non-root user SHALL be used to run the application\n144: - **AND** files SHALL be owned by the non-root user with appropriate permissions\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Security context configuration\n147: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n148: - **WHEN** examining security configurations\n149: - **THEN** file permissions SHALL be restrictive (e.g., 755, 644)\n150: - **AND** sensitive files SHALL NOT be included in image\n151: - **AND** no secrets or credentials SHALL be embedded in the image\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Component-specific multi-stage builds\n154: \n155: The system SHALL implement appropriate multi-stage builds for each AgentCube component.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Controller Manager multi-stage build\n158: - **GIVEN** the Controller Manager Dockerfile\n159: - **WHEN** the build is executed\n160: - **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n161: - **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n162: - **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n163: - **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Workload Manager multi-stage build\n166: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager Dockerfile\n167: - **WHEN** the build is executed\n168: - **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n169: - **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n170: - **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n171: - **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Router multi-stage build\n174: - **GIVEN** the Router Dockerfile\n175: - **WHEN** the build is executed\n176: - **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n177: - **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n178: - **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n179: - **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Component build consistency\n182: - **GIVEN** all AgentCube component Dockerfiles\n183: - **WHEN** comparing the Dockerfile structures\n184: - **THEN** all components SHALL use the same multi-stage pattern\n185: - **AND** all components SHALL use the same Go version\n186: - **AND** all components SHALL use the same runtime base image\n187: \n188: ### Requirement: Build arguments and versioning\n189: \n190: The system SHALL support build arguments for version control and customization.\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Build arguments for Go version\n193: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n194: - **WHEN** ARG instructions are used\n195: - **THEN** GO_VERSION SHALL be defined as an ARG\n196: - **AND** GO_VERSION SHALL have a default value (e.g., 1.21)\n197: - **AND** GO_VERSION SHALL be used in FROM statements\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Build arguments for component version\n200: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n201: - **WHEN** ARG instructions are used\n202: - **THEN** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be defined as an ARG\n203: - **AND** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be used for labeling\n204: - **AND** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be used for version-specific build steps\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Labels for image metadata\n207: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n208: - **WHEN** LABEL instructions are present\n209: - **THEN** maintainer label SHALL be set\n210: - **AND** version label SHALL be set\n211: - **AND** description label SHALL be set\n212: - **AND** labels SHALL be consistent across components\n213: \n214: ### Requirement: Health and readiness checks\n215: \n216: The system SHALL include health and readiness checks in the runtime stage.\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Health check endpoint configuration\n219: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n220: - **WHEN** HEALTHCHECK instruction is present\n221: - **THEN** HEALTHCHECK SHALL be configured\n222: - **AND** health check interval SHALL be specified (e.g., --interval=30s)\n223: - **AND** health check timeout SHALL be specified (e.g., --timeout=3s)\n224: - **AND** health check retries SHALL be specified (e.g., --retries=3)\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Health check command uses appropriate protocol\n227: - **GIVEN** the HEALTHCHECK instruction\n228: - **WHEN** examining the health check command\n229: - **THEN** the command SHALL use curl or wget (if available)\n230: - **OR** the command SHALL use a built-in health endpoint\n231: - **AND** the command SHALL check the component's health endpoint (e.g., /healthz, /health)\n232: \n233: ### Requirement: Multi-platform build support\n234: \n235: The system SHALL support multi-platform builds through appropriate base image selection.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Base images support multiple architectures\n238: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n239: - **WHEN** selecting base images\n240: - **THEN** builder stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., golang:1.21)\n241: - **AND** dependency stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., debian:bookworm-slim)\n242: - **AND** runtime stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., distroless)\n243: - **AND** images SHALL be buildable for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Cross-compilation in builder stage\n246: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n247: - **WHEN** building for different architectures\n248: - **THEN** the build process SHALL support cross-compilation\n249: - **AND** GOARCH and GOOS environment variables SHALL be respected\n250: - **AND** the binary SHALL be compiled for the target architecture\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: Build context and .dockerignore\n253: \n254: The system SHALL optimize build context using .dockerignore file.\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: .dockerignore excludes unnecessary files\n257: - **GIVEN** the .dockerignore file\n258: - **WHEN** examining its contents\n259: - **THEN** .git/ directory SHALL be excluded\n260: - **AND** README.md SHALL be excluded\n261: - **AND** *.md files SHALL be excluded\n262: - **AND** test files SHALL be excluded (e.g., *_test.go)\n263: - **AND** .dockerignore file SHALL be excluded\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Build context is minimal\n266: - **GIVEN** the Docker build command\n267: - **WHEN** the build context is analyzed\n268: - **THEN** only necessary files SHALL be included in build context\n269: - **AND** large unnecessary files SHALL be excluded via .dockerignore\n270: - **AND** build context size SHALL be minimized\n271: \n272: ### Requirement: Entrypoint and command configuration\n273: \n274: The system SHALL properly configure entrypoint and command in the runtime stage.\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Entrypoint uses the compiled binary\n277: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n278: - **WHEN** ENTRYPOINT instruction is set\n279: - **THEN** ENTRYPOINT SHALL point to the compiled binary\n280: - **AND** the binary path SHALL be absolute (e.g., /app/controller-manager)\n281: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: CMD supports default arguments\n284: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n285: - **WHEN** CMD instruction is set\n286: - **THEN** CMD SHALL provide default arguments\n287: - **AND** default arguments SHALL be sensible for the component\n288: - **AND** CMD arguments can be overridden at runtime\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Entrypoint script for initialization (optional)\n291: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage with an entrypoint script\n292: - **WHEN** an entrypoint script is used\n293: - **THEN** the script SHALL be copied from dependency stage\n294: - **AND** the script SHALL be executable\n295: - **AND** the script SHALL perform necessary initialization\n296: - **AND** the script SHALL exec the main binary at the end\n297: \n298: ### Requirement: Cache and volume configuration\n299: \n300: The system SHALL configure appropriate cache mounts and volumes for build optimization.\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Build cache for Go modules\n303: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n304: - **WHEN** building Go dependencies\n305: - **THEN** --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod SHALL be used for go mod download\n306: - **AND** build cache SHALL persist across builds\n307: - **AND** dependency download time SHALL be reduced\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Build cache for Go build\n310: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n311: - **WHEN** building the Go binary\n312: - **THEN** --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build SHALL be used for go build\n313: - **AND** incremental builds SHALL be faster\n314: - **AND** compiled object files SHALL be cached\n315: \n316: ### Requirement: Reproducible builds\n317: \n318: The system SHALL support reproducible builds through proper Dockerfile practices.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Fixed versions in base images\n321: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n322: - **WHEN** specifying base images\n323: - **THEN** base images SHALL use specific tags (e.g., golang:1.21.5)\n324: - **OR** base images SHALL use digests for complete reproducibility\n325: - **AND** latest tag SHALL NOT be used\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Deterministic build process\n328: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n329: - **WHEN** examining build instructions\n330: - **THEN** time and random factors SHALL be minimized\n331: - **AND** build timestamps SHALL be normalized if possible\n332: - **AND** the build SHALL produce identical outputs given same inputs\n333: \n334: ### Requirement: Documentation and comments\n335: \n336: The system SHALL provide clear documentation within the Dockerfile.\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Dockerfile has descriptive comments\n339: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n340: - **WHEN** examining comments\n341: - **THEN** each stage SHALL have a comment describing its purpose\n342: - **AND** complex build steps SHALL have explanatory comments\n343: - **AND** non-obvious COPY commands SHALL have comments\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Dockerfile follows best practices\n346: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n347: - **WHEN** reviewing against Dockerfile best practices\n348: - **THEN** .dockerignore SHALL be present\n349: - **AND** instructions SHALL be ordered for optimal caching\n350: - **AND** layers SHALL be minimized\n351: - **AND** multi-stage build SHALL be used effectively\n352: - **AND** security best practices SHALL be followed\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ## Backward Compatibility\n357: \n358: This delta specification defines multi-stage Dockerfile builds for the AgentCube project. The multi-stage builds are an optimization over existing single-stage builds and produce the same runtime images with improved efficiency and security. The final runtime images maintain compatibility with existing deployments, as they contain the same binaries and dependencies.\n359: \n360: ## Dependencies\n361: \n362: This delta specification depends on:\n363: - Docker 20.10+ (for multi-stage build support)\n364: - Go 1.21+ (for building AgentCube components)\n365: - Base design document: `design.md`\n366: - Base specification document: `deployment/spec.md`\n367: - AR: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values (for image configuration)\n368: \n369: ## Breaking Changes\n370: \n371: None. This delta specification defines an optimized build process using multi-stage Docker builds. The final runtime images remain compatible with existing deployments, and the build process change does not affect runtime behavior or API compatibility.\n372: \n373: ## Security Considerations\n374: \n375: 1. **Minimal Runtime Images**: Using distroless or minimal base images reduces the attack surface by excluding package managers, shells, and unnecessary tools.\n376: 2. **No Secrets in Images**: Multi-stage builds ensure no secrets or credentials are embedded in the final image, as secrets are only used in the builder stage and never copied to runtime.\n377: 3. **Non-Root Execution**: The runtime stage runs as a non-root user, reducing the impact of container escape vulnerabilities.\n378: 4. **Limited Permissions**: File permissions are restrictive, and the container has minimal privileges.\n379: 5. **Reproducible Builds**: Using specific image versions and digests ensures reproducible, verifiable builds.\n380: 6. **Build Isolation**: The builder and dependency stages are not included in the final image, isolating build-time dependencies.\n381: 7. **CVE Scanning**: Minimal images are easier to scan for vulnerabilities and have fewer CVEs to manage.\n382: \n383: ## Testing Strategy\n384: \n385: ### Build Tests\n386: - Verify multi-stage builds complete successfully for all components\n387: - Verify build artifacts are correctly transferred between stages\n388: - Verify final images contain only necessary files\n389: - Verify build cache improves incremental build times\n390: \n391: ### Image Size Tests\n392: - Measure final image size for each component\n393: - Compare with single-stage build size\n394: - Verify size reduction meets expectations (>50% reduction)\n395: - Verify builder and dependency stages are not in final image\n396: \n397: ### Security Tests\n398: - Scan final images for CVEs using tools like Trivy or Snyk\n399: - Verify runtime images use distroless or minimal base\n400: - Verify no build tools are present in runtime images\n401: - Verify non-root user is configured correctly\n402: - Verify no secrets or credentials in final image\n403: \n404: ### Functional Tests\n405: - Run containers built with multi-stage Dockerfiles\n406: - Verify containers start and run correctly\n407: - Verify health checks work as expected\n408: - Verify components can communicate with each other\n409: - Verify all functionality works as expected\n410: \n411: ### Multi-Platform Tests\n412: - Build images for linux/amd64\n413: - Build images for linux/arm64\n414: - Verify images run correctly on both architectures\n415: - Verify cross-compilation works correctly\n416: \n417: ### Cache Tests\n418: - Verify Go module cache works correctly\n419: - Verify Go build cache works correctly\n420: - Measure cache hit/miss rates\n421: - Verify incremental builds are faster\n422: \n423: ### Reproducibility Tests\n424: - Build the same image twice and compare\n425: - Verify images are identical using digests\n426: - Verify build output is deterministic\n427: - Verify using image tags and digests produces reproducible results\n428: \n429: ### Integration Tests\n430: - Test multi-stage builds in CI/CD pipeline\n431: - Verify builds work with Docker BuildKit\n432: - Verify builds work with Buildah (if applicable)\n433: - Verify image signing and verification (if implemented)\n\n(End of file - total 433 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-032\n- **Title**: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n- **Module**: docker\n- **Language**: Dockerfile\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for Dockerfile multi-stage builds with 3 images in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for building AgentCube components using multi-stage Docker builds to optimize image size, build time, and security. The specification covers three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime stages, with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to ensure proper implementation of the multi-stage build pattern.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Multi-stage build structure with three stages\n\nThe system SHALL implement Dockerfile multi-stage builds with three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883629451,"end":1775883629467}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883629474,"sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9b36d00124j2T4FGpsaDaG","messageID":"msg_d7ae9a1aa001R9CjofZaUQoZRr","sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bd22b288f125494ea4f75b547fa3c785","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `docker`\n4: **Language**: Dockerfile\n5: **Size**: S\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Create .dockerignore file\n11: - [ ] Create .dockerignore file in project root\n12: - [ ] Add .git directory to exclude\n13: - [ ] Add *.md files to exclude (README.md, docs/)\n14: - [ ] Add test files (*_test.go, pytest.ini, .coverage)\n15: - [ ] Add development files (.vscode/, .idea/, *.swp)\n16: - [ ] Add build artifacts (dist/, build/, *.exe)\n17: - [ ] Add CI/CD files (.github/, .gitlab-ci.yml)\n18: - [ ] Add OS files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db)\n19: - [ ] Add temporary files (tmp/, temp/, *.tmp)\n20: - [ ] Add .dockerignore itself to exclude\n21: \n22: **Verification**:\n23: ```bash\n24: test -f .dockerignore && echo \".dockerignore exists\" || echo \"Missing\"\n25: grep -q \"\\.git\" .dockerignore && echo \"Git excluded\" || echo \"Git not excluded\"\n26: grep -q \"*_test\\.go\" .dockerignore && echo \"Test files excluded\" || echo \"Test files not excluded\"\n27: ```\n28: \n29: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n30: - .dockerignore file exists in project root\n31: - Contains all required exclusion patterns\n32: - Build context is minimized (verify with docker build context size)\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### Task 2: Create Dockerfile build arguments section\n37: - [ ] Create Dockerfile in project root\n38: - [ ] Add ARG GO_VERSION with default value 1.21\n39: - [ ] Add ARG ALPINE_VERSION with default value 3.19\n40: - [ ] Add ARG BUILD_VERSION with default value dev\n41: - [ ] Add ARG BUILD_TIME for build timestamp\n42: - [ ] Add ARG GIT_COMMIT for git commit hash\n43: - [ ] Add comment block explaining build arguments\n44: - [ ] Document build argument usage\n45: \n46: **Verification**:\n47: ```bash\n48: grep -q \"ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\" Dockerfile && echo \"GO_VERSION defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\n49: grep -q \"ARG BUILD_VERSION=dev\" Dockerfile && echo \"BUILD_VERSION defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\n50: grep -q \"ARG BUILD_TIME\" Dockerfile && echo \"BUILD_TIME defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\n51: grep -q \"ARG GIT_COMMIT\" Dockerfile && echo \"GIT_COMMIT defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\n52: ```\n53: \n54: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n55: - All 5 build arguments are defined\n56: - Default values are set for GO_VERSION, ALPINE_VERSION, BUILD_VERSION\n57: - Comments explain each build argument's purpose\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ### Task 3: Create builder stage FROM statement\n62: - [ ] Add builder stage FROM statement using golang:${GO_VERSION}-alpine\n63: - [ ] Name the stage AS builder\n64: - [ ] Add comment describing builder stage purpose\n65: - [ ] Copy build arguments into builder stage (BUILD_VERSION, BUILD_TIME, GIT_COMMIT)\n66: \n67: **Verification**:\n68: ```bash\n69: grep -q \"FROM golang:\\${GO_VERSION}-alpine AS builder\" Dockerfile && echo \"Builder FROM correct\" || echo \"Builder FROM incorrect\"\n70: ```\n71: \n72: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n73: - Builder stage uses golang:1.21-alpine base image\n74: - Stage is named \"builder\"\n75: - Comment describes stage purpose\n76: - Build arguments are available in builder stage\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ### Task 4: Install build tools in builder stage\n81: - [ ] Add RUN apk add --no-cache command\n82: - [ ] Install python3 package\n83: - [ ] Install py3-pip package\n84: - [ ] Install gcc package\n85: - [ ] Install musl-dev package\n86: - [ ] Install git package\n87: - [ ] Combine all packages in single RUN instruction for layer optimization\n88: - [ ] Clean up package cache in same RUN instruction\n89: \n90: **Verification**:\n91: ```bash\n92: grep -A 3 \"RUN apk add --no-cache\" Dockerfile | grep -q \"python3\" && echo \"Python installed\" || echo \"Python missing\"\n93: grep -A 3 \"RUN apk add --no-cache\" Dockerfile | grep -q \"gcc\" && echo \"GCC installed\" || echo \"GCC missing\"\n94: ```\n95: \n96: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n97: - All required build tools are installed\n98: - Single RUN instruction with --no-cache flag\n99: - Package cache is cleaned up\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Task 5: Set working directory in builder stage\n104: - [ ] Add WORKDIR /build instruction\n105: - [ ] Add comment explaining working directory choice\n106: \n107: **Verification**:\n108: ```bash\n109: grep -q \"WORKDIR /build\" Dockerfile && echo \"Working directory set\" || echo \"Working directory missing\"\n110: ```\n111: \n112: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n113: - Working directory is set to /build\n114: - Comment explains the choice\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ### Task 6: Copy Go dependencies for caching optimization\n119: - [ ] Add COPY go.mod go.sum ./ instruction\n120: - [ ] Add comment explaining caching optimization\n121: - [ ] Add RUN go mod download instruction\n122: - [ ] Verify dependency manifests are copied before source code\n123: \n124: **Verification**:\n125: ```bash\n126: grep -q \"COPY go.mod go.sum \\./\" Dockerfile && echo \"Go deps copied first\" || echo \"Go deps not first\"\n127: grep -q \"RUN go mod download\" Dockerfile && echo \"Go mod download present\" || echo \"Go mod download missing\"\n128: ```\n129: \n130: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n131: - go.mod and go.sum are copied before source code\n132: - go mod download is run immediately after copying manifests\n133: - Comment explains caching optimization\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ### Task 7: Copy Go source code\n138: - [ ] Add COPY ./pkg ./pkg instruction\n139: - [ ] Add COPY ./cmd ./cmd instruction\n140: - [ ] Add comment explaining source code structure\n141: - [ ] Ensure source code is copied after dependencies are installed\n142: \n143: **Verification**:\n144: ```bash\n145: grep -q \"COPY \\./pkg \\./pkg\" Dockerfile && echo \"pkg copied\" || echo \"pkg not copied\"\n146: grep -q \"COPY \\./cmd \\./cmd\" Dockerfile && echo \"cmd copied\" || echo \"cmd not copied\"\n147: ```\n148: \n149: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n150: - pkg directory is copied\n151: - cmd directory is copied\n152: - Source code is copied after dependency installation\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ### Task 8: Build agentd binary with version info\n157: - [ ] Add RUN go build instruction\n158: - [ ] Set CGO_ENABLED=0 environment variable\n159: - [ ] Set GOOS=linux environment variable\n160: - [ ] Add -ldflags=\"-s -w\" for binary size optimization\n161: - [ ] Add -X main.Version=${BUILD_VERSION} to embed version\n162: - [ ] Add -X main.BuildTime=${BUILD_TIME} to embed build time\n163: - [ ] Add -X main.GitCommit=${GIT_COMMIT} to embed commit hash\n164: - [ ] Set output path as -o agentd\n165: - [ ] Set build path as ./cmd/agentd\n166: - [ ] Add comment explaining build flags and version embedding\n167: \n168: **Verification**:\n169: ```bash\n170: grep -q \"CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build\" Dockerfile && echo \"Go build correct\" || echo \"Go build incorrect\"\n171: grep -q \"main.Version=\\${BUILD_VERSION}\" Dockerfile && echo \"Version embedding\" || echo \"Version not embedded\"\n172: grep -q \"-ldflags=\\\"-s -w\\\"\" Dockerfile && echo \"Size optimization\" || echo \"Size optimization missing\"\n173: ```\n174: \n175: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n176: - Binary is built with CGO_ENABLED=0 and GOOS=linux\n177: - -s -w flags are used for size optimization\n178: - Version, build time, and commit are embedded\n179: - Output binary is named agentd\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ### Task 9: Copy Python source and requirements\n184: - [ ] Add COPY ./cmd/picod /build/picod instruction\n185: - [ ] Add COPY requirements.txt ./ instruction\n186: - [ ] Add comment explaining Python component structure\n187: - [ ] Ensure Python dependencies are copied after Go source code\n188: \n189: **Verification**:\n190: ```bash\n191: grep -q \"COPY \\./cmd/picod /build/picod\" Dockerfile && echo \"Python source copied\" || echo \"Python source missing\"\n192: grep -q \"COPY requirements\\.txt \\./\" Dockerfile && echo \"Requirements copied\" || echo \"Requirements missing\"\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n196: - picod source directory is copied\n197: - requirements.txt is copied\n198: - Comment explains Python component structure\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ### Task 10: Install Python dependencies\n203: - [ ] Add RUN pip install instruction\n204: - [ ] Use --no-cache-dir flag to reduce image size\n205: - [ ] Install from requirements.txt with -r requirements.txt\n206: - [ ] Add comment explaining --no-cache-dir optimization\n207: \n208: **Verification**:\n209: ```bash\n210: grep -q \"RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements\\.txt\" Dockerfile && echo \"Python deps installed\" || echo \"Python deps missing\"\n211: ```\n212: \n213: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n214: - Python dependencies are installed from requirements.txt\n215: - --no-cache-dir flag is used\n216: - Comment explains optimization\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### Task 11: Create verifier stage (optional)\n221: - [ ] Add verifier stage FROM builder AS verifier\n222: - [ ] Add comment describing verifier stage purpose\n223: - [ ] Add RUN go test ./... -v -coverprofile=coverage.out instruction\n224: - [ ] Add RUN pytest /build/picod/tests -v instruction\n225: - [ ] Add RUN go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html instruction\n226: - [ ] Add comments explaining each test execution\n227: \n228: **Verification**:\n229: ``