AL agentcube:latest\n801: ```\n802: \n803: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n804: - No CRITICAL vulnerabilities (or documented and accepted)\n805: - No HIGH vulnerabilities (or documented and accepted)\n806: - Vulnerability report is generated\n807: - Security posture is documented\n808: \n809: ---\n810: \n811: ### Task 40: Verify reproducible builds\n812: - [ ] Build image with specific versions\n813: - [ ] Record image digest\n814: - [ ] Build image again with same parameters\n815: - [ ] Compare image digests\n816: - [ ] Verify digests are identical\n817: \n818: **Verification**:\n819: ```bash\n820: DIGEST1=$(docker build --quiet -t agentcube:repro1 .)\n821: DIGEST2=$(docker build --quiet -t agentcube:repro2 .)\n822: echo \"Digest 1: $DIGEST1\"\n823: echo \"Digest 2: $DIGEST2\"\n824: [ \"$DIGEST1\" = \"$DIGEST2\" ] && echo \"Builds are reproducible\" || echo \"Builds differ\"\n825: ```\n826: \n827: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n828: - Both builds produce identical digests\n829: - Builds are deterministic\n830: - No random factors affect build output\n831: \n832: ---\n833: \n834: ### Task 41: Create documentation\n835: - [ ] Create docs/docker.md\n836: - [ ] Document build process\n837: - [ ] Document build arguments\n838: - [ ] Document image variants\n839: - [ ] Provide usage examples\n840: - [ ] Document health check endpoints\n841: - [ ] Document metrics endpoints\n842: \n843: **Verification**:\n844: ```bash\n845: test -f docs/docker.md && echo \"Documentation exists\" || echo \"Documentation missing\"\n846: grep -q \"Build Process\" docs/docker.md && echo \"Build process documented\" || echo \"Build process not documented\"\n847: ```\n848: \n849: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n850: - Documentation file exists\n851: - Build process is documented\n852: - Build arguments are documented\n853: - Usage examples are provided\n854: - API endpoints are documented\n855: \n856: ---\n857: \n858: ### Task 42: Update README.md\n859: - [ ] Update README.md with Docker build section\n860: - [