{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883669287,"sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","part":{"id":"prt_d7aea4385001InRM6SC1ZQA1CD","messageID":"msg_d7aea1351001Gd4qSSdCFV5KvU","sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e56a32dbe3eb4aa2ab22837b44dae9a8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/test.sh"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/test.sh</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/bin/bash\n2: # Test script for AR-032 multi-stage Dockerfile build\n3: \n4: set -e\n5: \n6: # Colors for output\n7: RED='\\033[0;31m'\n8: GREEN='\\033[0;32m'\n9: YELLOW='\\033[1;33m'\n10: BLUE='\\033[0;34m'\n11: NC='\\033[0m' # No Color\n12: \n13: log_info() {\n14:     echo -e \"${BLUE}[TEST]${NC} $1\"\n15: }\n16: \n17: log_success() {\n18:     echo -e \"${GREEN}[PASS]${NC} $1\"\n19: }\n20: \n21: log_error() {\n22:     echo -e \"${RED}[FAIL]${NC} $1\"\n23: }\n24: \n25: log_warn() {\n26:     echo -e \"${YELLOW}[WARN]${NC} $1\"\n27: }\n28: \n29: # Test counters\n30: TESTS_PASSED=0\n31: TESTS_FAILED=0\n32: TESTS_TOTAL=0\n33: \n34: # Test function\n35: run_test() {\n36:     local test_name=\"$1\"\n37:     local test_command=\"$2\"\n38:     \n39:     TESTS_TOTAL=$((TESTS_TOTAL + 1))\n40:     log_info \"Running: $test_name\"\n41:     \n42:     if eval \"$test_command\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n43:         log_success \"$test_name\"\n44:         TESTS_PASSED=$((TESTS_PASSED + 1))\n45:         return 0\n46:     else\n47:         log_error \"$test_name\"\n48:         TESTS_FAILED=$((TESTS_FAILED + 1))\n49:         return 1\n50:     fi\n51: }\n52: \n53: # Change to script directory\n54: cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\"\n55: \n56: echo \"==========================================\"\n57: echo \"AR-032 Dockerfile Test Suite\"\n58: echo \"==========================================\"\n59: echo \"\"\n60: \n61: # ========================================\n62: # Phase 1: File Structure Tests\n63: # ========================================\n64: echo \"Phase 1: File Structure Tests\"\n65: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n66: \n67: run_test \"Dockerfile exists\" \"test -f Dockerfile\"\n68: run_test \".dockerignore exists\" \"test -f .dockerignore\"\n69: run_test \"requirements.txt exists\" \"test -f requirements.txt\"\n70: run_test \"build.sh exists and is executable\" \"test -x build.sh\"\n71: run_test \"build-multiarch.sh exists and is executable\" \"test -x build-multiarch.sh\"\n72: run_test \"validate-build.sh exists and is executable\" \"test -x validate-build.sh\"\n73: run_test \"validate-runtime.sh exists and is executable\" \"test -x validate-runtime.sh\"\n74: run_test \"README.md exists\" \"test -f README.md\"\n75: \n76: echo \"\"\n77: \n78: # ========================================\n79: # Phase 2: Dockerfile Syntax Tests\n80: # ========================================\n81: echo \"Phase 2: Dockerfile Syntax Tests\"\n82: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n83: \n84: run_test \"Dockerfile is not empty\" \"test -s Dockerfile\"\n85: run_test \"Dockerfile has FROM instruction\" \"grep -q '^FROM' Dockerfile\"\n86: run_test \"Dockerfile has builder stage\" \"grep -q 'AS builder' Dockerfile\"\n87: run_test \"Dockerfile has verifier stage\" \"grep -q 'AS verifier' Dockerfile\"\n88: run_test \"Dockerfile has runtime stage\" \"grep -q 'AS runtime' Dockerfile\"\n89: run_test \"Dockerfile has build arguments\" \"grep -q '^ARG' Dockerfile\"\n90: run_test \"Dockerfile has WORKDIR\" \"grep -q 'WORKDIR' Dockerfile\"\n91: run_test \"Dockerfile has COPY instructions\" \"grep -q '^COPY' Dockerfile\"\n92: run_test \"Dockerfile has RUN instructions\" \"grep -q '^RUN' Dockerfile\"\n93: run_test \"Dockerfile has EXPOSE\" \"grep -q '^EXPOSE' Dockerfile\"\n94: run_test \"Dockerfile has USER\" \"grep -q '^USER' Dockerfile\"\n95: run_test \"Dockerfile has ENTRYPOINT\" \"grep -q '^ENTRYPOINT' Dockerfile\"\n96: run_test \"Dockerfile has HEALTHCHECK\" \"grep -q '^HEALTHCHECK' Dockerfile\"\n97: run_test \"Dockerfile has LABEL\" \"grep -q '^LABEL' Dockerfile\"\n98: run_test \"Dockerfile has ENV\" \"grep -q '^ENV' Dockerfile\"\n99: \n100: echo \"\"\n101: \n102: # ========================================\n103: # Phase 3: .dockerignore Tests\n104: # ========================================\n105: echo \"Phase 3: .dockerignore Tests\"\n106: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n107: \n108: run_test \".dockerignore is not empty\" \"test -s .dockerignore\"\n109: run_test \".dockerignore excludes .git\" \"grep -q '^\\.git' .dockerignore\"\n110: run_test \".dockerignore excludes *.md\" \"grep -q '\\*\\.md' .dockerignore\"\n111: run_test \".dockerignore excludes test files\" \"grep -q '_test\\.go' .dockerignore\"\n112: run_test \".dockerignore excludes .github\" \"grep -q '\\.github' .dockerignore\"\n113: \n114: echo \"\"\n115: \n116: # ========================================\n117: # Phase 4: requirements.txt Tests\n118: # ========================================\n119: echo \"Phase 4: requirements.txt Tests\"\n120: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n121: \n122: run_test \"requirements.txt is not empty\" \"test -s requirements.txt\"\n123: run_test \"requirements.txt has pyyaml\" \"grep -q 'pyyaml' requirements.txt\"\n124: run_test \"requirements.txt has pydantic\" \"grep -q 'pydantic' requirements.txt\"\n125: \n126: echo \"\"\n127: \n128: # ========================================\n129: # Phase 5: Build Script Tests\n130: # ========================================\n131: echo \"Phase 5: Build Script Tests\"\n132: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n133: \n134: run_test \"build.sh has shebang\" \"head -1 build.sh | grep -q '#!/bin/bash'\"\n135: run_test \"build.sh has set -e\" \"grep -q 'set -e' build.sh\"\n136: run_test \"build.sh has GO_VERSION variable\" \"grep -q 'GO_VERSION' build.sh\"\n137: run_test \"build.sh has BUILD_VERSION variable\" \"grep -q 'BUILD_VERSION' build.sh\"\n138: run_test \"build-multiarch.sh has shebang\" \"head -1 build-multiarch.sh | grep -q '#!/bin/bash'\"\n139: run_test \"build-multiarch.sh has set -e\" \"grep -q 'set -e' build-multiarch.sh\"\n140: run_test \"build-multiarch.sh has PLATFORMS variable\" \"grep -q 'PLATFORMS' build-multiarch.sh\"\n141: \n142: echo \"\"\n143: \n144: # ========================================\n145: # Phase 6: Validation Script Tests\n146: # ========================================\n147: echo \"Phase 6: Validation Script Tests\"\n148: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n149: \n150: run_test \"validate-build.sh has shebang\" \"head -1 validate-build.sh | grep -q '#!/bin/bash'\"\n151: run_test \"validate-build.sh checks Dockerfile syntax\" \"grep -q 'docker build --check' validate-build.sh\"\n152: run_test \"validate-runtime.sh has shebang\" \"head -1 validate-runtime.sh | grep -q '#!/bin/bash'\"\n153: run_test \"validate-runtime.sh checks container status\" \"grep -q 'docker inspect' validate-runtime.sh\"\n154: \n155: echo \"\"\n156: \n157: # ========================================\n158: # Phase 7: README Tests\n159: # ========================================\n160: echo \"Phase 7: README Tests\"\n161: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n162: \n163: run_test \"README.md is not empty\" \"test -s README.md\"\n164: run_test \"README.md has Quick Start section\" \"grep -q 'Quick Start' README.md\"\n165: run_test \"README.md has Build Targets section\" \"grep -q 'Build Targets' README.md\"\n166: run_test \"README.md has Usage section\" \"grep -q 'Usage Examples' README.md\"\n167: run_test \"README.md has Security section\" \"grep -q 'Security' README.md\"\n168: \n169: echo \"\"\n170: \n171: # ========================================\n172: # Phase 8: Docker Build Tests (if Docker available)\n173: # ========================================\n174: echo \"Phase 8: Docker Build Tests\"\n175: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n176: \n177: if command -v docker &> /dev/null; then\n178:     run_test \"Docker daemon is running\" \"docker info >/dev/null 2>&1\"\n179:     \n180:     # Test Dockerfile syntax check (may fail if Docker version doesn't support --check)\n181:     if docker build --check . >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n182:         run_test \"Dockerfile syntax check passes\" \"true\"\n183:     else\n184:         log_warn \"Dockerfile syntax check not supported by Docker version\"\n185:         TESTS_TOTAL=$((TESTS_TOTAL - 1))\n186:     fi\n187:     \n188:     # Test base image pull\n189:     if docker pull golang:1.21-alpine >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n190:         run_test \"Base image golang:1.21-alpine is available\" \"true\"\n191:     else\n192:         log_warn \"Could not pull base image (may be network issue)\"\n193:         TESTS_TOTAL=$((TESTS_TOTAL - 1))\n194:     fi\n195:     \n196:     if docker pull alpine:3.19 >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n197:         run_test \"Base image alpine:3.19 is available\" \"true\"\n198:     else\n199:         log_warn \"Could not pull base image (may be network issue)\"\n200:         TESTS_TOTAL=$((TESTS_TOTAL - 1))\n201:     fi\n202: else\n203:     log_warn \"Docker is not available, skipping Docker build tests\"\n204: fi\n205: \n206: echo \"\"\n207: \n208: # ========================================\n209: # Phase 9: Image Configuration Tests\n210: # ========================================\n211: echo \"Phase 9: Image Configuration Tests\"\n212: echo \"----------------------------------------\"\n213: \n214: run_test \"Dockerfile specifies non-root user\" \"grep -q 'USER agentcube' Dockerfile\"\n215: run_test \"Dockerfile has WORKDIR /app\" \"grep -q 'WORKDIR /app' Dockerfile\"\n216: run_test \"Dockerfile exposes port 8080\" \"grep -q 'EXPOSE.*8080' Dockerfile\"\n217: run_test \"Dockerfile exposes port 9090\" \"grep -q 'EXPOSE.*9090' Dockerfile\"\n218: run_test \"Dockerfile has maintainer label\" \"grep -q 'maintainer' Dockerfile\"\n219: run_test \"Dockerfile has version label\" \"grep -q 'version' Dockerfile\"\n220: \n221: echo \"\"\n222: \n223: # ========================================\n224: # Test Results Summary\n225: # ========================================\n226: echo \"==========================================\"\n227: echo \"Test Results Summary\"\n228: echo \"==========================================\"\n229: echo \"\"\n230: echo \"Total Tests:  $TESTS_TOTAL\"\n231: echo -e \"Passed:       ${GREEN}$TESTS_PASSED${NC}\"\n232: if [ $TESTS_FAILED -gt 0 ]; then\n233:     echo -e \"Failed:       ${RED}$TESTS_FAILED${NC}\"\n234: else\n235:     echo -e \"Failed:       $TESTS_FAILED\"\n236: fi\n237: echo \"\"\n238: \n239: if [ $TESTS_FAILED -eq 0 ]; then\n240:     log_success \"All tests passed!\"\n241:     exit 0\n242: else\n243:     log_error \"Some tests failed!\"\n244:     exit 1\n245: fi\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/bin/bash\n# Test script for AR-032 multi-stage Dockerfile build\n\nset -e\n\n# Colors for output\nRED='\\033[0;31m'\nGREEN='\\033[0;32m'\nYELLOW='\\033[1;33m'\nBLUE='\\033[0;34m'\nNC='\\033[0m' # No Color\n\nlog_info() {\n    echo -e \"${BLUE}[TEST]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\nlog_success() {\n    echo -e \"${GREEN}[PASS]${NC} $1\"\n}\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/test.sh","time":{"start":1775883669266,"end":1775883669286}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883669289,"sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","part":{"id":"prt_d7aea49040010Otsg5fJXXIMS4","messageID":"msg_d7aea1351001Gd4qSSdCFV5KvU","sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8fc27d842cda441d8ce1ebd68cf958de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/.dockerignore"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/.dockerignore</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Git files\n2: .git\n3: .gitignore\n4: .gitattributes\n5: \n6: # Documentation\n7: *.md\n8: docs/\n9: \n10: # Development files\n11: .vscode/\n12: .idea/\n13: *.swp\n14: *.swo\n15: \n16: # Build artifacts\n17: dist/\n18: build/\n19: *.exe\n20: *.dll\n21: *.dylib\n22: \n23: # Test files\n24: *_test.go\n25: pytest.ini\n26: .coverage\n27: .coverage.*\n28: \n29: # CI/CD\n30: .github/\n31: .gitlab-ci.yml\n32: .travis.yml\n33: \n34: # IDE\n35: .vscode/\n36: .idea/\n37: \n38: # OS\n39: .DS_Store\n40: Thumbs.db\n41: \n42: # Temporary files\n43: tmp/\n44: temp/\n45: *.tmp\n46: \n47: # Docker files (except Dockerfile)\n48: docker-compose*.yml\n49: *.dockerfile\n50: \n51: # Node modules (if any)\n52: node_modules/\n53: \n54: # Python cache\n55: __pycache__/\n56: *.py[cod]\n57: *$py.class\n58: .Python\n59: venv/\n60: env/\n61: \n62: # Go cache\n63: *.sum\n64: go.sum\n\n(End of file - total 64 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Git files\n.git\n.gitignore\n.gitattributes\n\n# Documentation\n*.md\ndocs/\n\n# Development files\n.vscode/\n.idea/\n*.swp\n*.swo\n\n# Build artifacts\ndist/\nbuild/\n*.exe\n*.dll","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/.dockerignore","time":{"start":1775883669270,"end":1775883669288}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883669293,"sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","part":{"id":"prt_d7aea4ef20011F3ADMs4Au0KLE","messageID":"msg_d7aea1351001Gd4qSSdCFV5KvU","sessionID":"ses_285169c88ffe90hQDn8Kg9pqnS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cccb1f9816de406ab76bca2d559f6654","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032: Dockerfile Multi-Stage Build - Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Implementation Status\n4: \n5: ✅ **COMPLETE** - All components implemented and tested\n6: \n7: ## Overview\n8: \n9: This implementation provides a comprehensive multi-stage Dockerfile build strategy for the AgentCube project, featuring three independent build stages (Builder, Verifier, Runtime) to create optimized production images.\n10: \n11: ## Files Created\n12: \n13: ### Core Docker Files\n14: - **Dockerfile** - Multi-stage Dockerfile with 3 build stages\n15: - **.dockerignore** - Build context exclusions\n16: - **requirements.txt** - Python dependencies for picod\n17: \n18: ### Build Scripts\n19: - **build.sh** - Single-architecture build script with multiple target support\n20: - **build-multiarch.sh** - Multi-architecture build script for linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n21: \n22: ### Validation Scripts\n23: - **validate-build.sh** - Comprehensive build validation (12 tests)\n24: - **validate-runtime.sh** - Runtime container validation (17 tests)\n25: - **test.sh** - Automated test suite (50+ tests)\n26: \n27: ### Documentation\n28: - **README.md** - Comprehensive user documentation\n29: - **IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md** - This file\n30: - **Makefile** - Convenient Make targets for common operations\n31: \n32: ## Architecture\n33: \n34: ### Build Stages\n35: \n36: #### Stage 1: Builder\n37: - **Base**: `golang:1.21-alpine`\n38: - **Purpose**: Compile binaries and install dependencies\n39: - **Output**: Development image (~800-1200 MB)\n40: - **Artifacts**:\n41:   - Compiled `agentd` binary\n42:   - Python site-packages\n43:   - PicoD source code\n44: \n45: #### Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)\n46: - **Base**: Inherits from builder\n47: - **Purpose**: Run tests and quality checks\n48: - **Output**: Test image (~850-1250 MB)\n49: - **Tests**:\n50:   - Go unit tests with coverage\n51:   - Python unit tests\n52:   - Test report generation\n53: \n54: #### Stage 3: Runtime\n55: - **Base**: `alpine:3.19`\n56: - **Purpose**: Production-ready minimal image\n57: - **Output**: Production image (~150-250 MB)\n58: - **Features**:\n59:   - Non-privileged user (agentcube:1000)\n60:   - Health checks\n61:   - Metrics endpoint\n62:   - Security hardening\n63: \n64: ## Build Arguments\n65: \n66: | Argument | Default | Description |\n67: |----------|---------|-------------|\n68: | `GO_VERSION` | `1.21` | Go compiler version |\n69: | `ALPINE_VERSION` | `3.19` | Alpine Linux version |\n70: | `BUILD_VERSION` | `dev` | Application version |\n71: | `BUILD_TIME` | (auto) | Build timestamp |\n72: | `GIT_COMMIT` | (auto) | Git commit hash |\n73: \n74: ## Environment Variables\n75: \n76: | Variable | Default | Description |\n77: |----------|---------|-------------|\n78: | `AGENTCUBE_ENV` | `production` | Runtime environment |\n79: | `AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL` | `info` | Logging level |\n80: | `AGENTCUBE_LOG_FORMAT` | `json` | Log format |\n81: | `AGENTCUBE_PORT` | `8080` | Service port |\n82: | `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enable metrics |\n83: | `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT` | `9090` | Metrics port |\n84: \n85: ## Security Features\n86: \n87: 1. **Non-privileged execution**: Runs as `agentcube` (UID 1000)\n88: 2. **Minimal base image**: Alpine Linux (~5MB)\n89: 3. **No build tools**: Compilers excluded from runtime\n90: 4. **Minimal dependencies**: Only runtime essentials\n91: 5. **Health checks**: Built-in health endpoint\n92: 6. **Secure labels**: OCI-compliant image labels\n93: \n94: ## Performance Optimizations\n95: \n96: 1. **Layer caching**: Optimized instruction ordering\n97: 2. **Dependency caching**: Go deps before source code\n98: 3. **Multi-stage**: Build tools discarded\n99: 4. **Binary stripping**: `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`\n100: 5. **No-cache pip**: Smaller Python layer\n101: \n102: ## Testing\n103: \n104: ### Build Validation Tests (12)\n105: 1. Dockerfile syntax check\n106: 2. Base image availability\n107: 3. Builder image build\n108: 4. Verifier image build\n109: 5. Runtime image build\n110: 6. Image size verification\n111: 7. Layer count check\n112: 8. Non-root user verification\n113: 9. Binary execution test\n114: 10. Image metadata check\n115: 11. Exposed ports verification\n116: 12. Healthcheck configuration\n117: \n118: ### Runtime Validation Tests (17)\n119: 1. Container startup\n120: 2. Container logs\n121: 3. Non-root user execution\n122: 4. Working directory\n123: 5. File permissions\n124: 6. File ownership\n125: 7. Binary availability\n126: 8. Python installation\n127: 9. Python packages\n128: 10. PicoD directory\n129: 11. Environment variables\n130: 12. Resource limits\n131: 13. Volume mounting\n132: 14. Network connectivity\n133: 15. Image size\n134: 16. Layer count\n135: 17. Base image verification\n136: \n137: ### Automated Test Suite (50+)\n138: - File structure tests\n139: - Dockerfile syntax tests\n140: - .dockerignore tests\n141: - requirements.txt tests\n142: - Build script tests\n143: - Validation script tests\n144: - README tests\n145: - Docker build tests\n146: - Image configuration tests\n147: \n148: ## Usage Examples\n149: \n150: ### Basic Build\n151: ```bash\n152: ./build.sh runtime\n153: # or\n154: make build\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### Build All Targets\n158: ```bash\n159: ./build.sh all\n160: # or\n161: make build-all\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### Multi-Architecture Build\n165: ```bash\n166: ./build-multiarch.sh --push --platforms linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n167: # or\n168: make build-multiarch-push\n169: ```\n170: \n171: ### Validate Build\n172: ```bash\n173: ./validate-build.sh\n174: # or\n175: make validate-build\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ### Validate Runtime\n179: ```bash\n180: ./validate-runtime.sh\n181: # or\n182: make validate-runtime\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ### Run Tests\n186: ```bash\n187: ./test.sh\n188: # or\n189: make test\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ### Run Container\n193: ```bash\n194: make run\n195: # or\n196: docker run -d -p 8080:8080 agentcube:latest\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ## Make Targets\n200: \n201: | Target | Description |\n202: |--------|-------------|\n203: | `help` | Show help message |\n204: | `build` | Build production runtime image |\n205: | `build-builder` | Build builder (development) image |\n206: | `build-verifier` | Build verifier (test) image |\n207: | `build-all` | Build all targets |\n208: | `build-multiarch` | Build multi-architecture images |\n209: | `build-multiarch-push` | Build and push multi-arch images |\n210: | `validate` | Run all validations |\n211: | `validate-build` | Validate build process |\n212: | `validate-runtime` | Validate runtime container |\n213: | `test` | Run test suite |\n214: | `clean` | Clean up Docker images |\n215: | `inspect` | Inspect built image |\n216: | `history` | Show image history |\n217: | `size` | Show image size |\n218: | `run` | Run the container |\n219: | `logs` | Show container logs |\n220: | `stop` | Stop running container |\n221: | `bash` | Open shell in container |\n222: | `push` | Push image to registry |\n223: | `scan` | Scan for vulnerabilities (Trivy) |\n224: | `lint` | Lint Dockerfile (Hadolint) |\n225: | `info` | Show build information |\n226: \n227: ## CI/CD Integration\n228: \n229: The implementation includes CI/CD-ready scripts that can be integrated with:\n230: - GitHub Actions\n231: - GitLab CI/CD\n232: - Jenkins\n233: - Other CI/CD platforms\n234: \n235: See README.md for GitHub Actions example.\n236: \n237: ## Metrics and Monitoring\n238: \n239: ### Exposed Ports\n240: - **8080**: Main application port\n241: - **9090**: Metrics endpoint (Prometheus format)\n242: \n243: ### Endpoints\n244: - `/healthz`: Health check endpoint\n245: - `/metrics`: Prometheus metrics endpoint\n246: \n247: ## Troubleshooting\n248: \n249: See README.md for comprehensive troubleshooting guide covering:\n250: - Build failures\n251: - Runtime failures\n252: - Permission errors\n253: - Network issues\n254: - Resource constraints\n255: \n256: ## Performance Metrics\n257: \n258: ### Target Metrics\n259: - **Build Time** (cached): < 5 minutes\n260: - **Image Size**: < 250 MB\n261: - **Layer Count**: < 15\n262: - **Cache Hit Rate**: > 70%\n263: - **Startup Time**: < 10 seconds\n264: - **Memory Usage**: < 200 MB\n265: \n266: ## Compliance\n267: \n268: ### Security Compliance\n269: - ✅ Non-root user execution\n270: - ✅ Minimal base image\n271: - ✅ No build tools in runtime\n272: - ✅ Secure file permissions\n273: - ✅ Health checks enabled\n274: \n275: ### Best Practices\n276: - ✅ Dockerfile best practices (Hadolint compliant)\n277: - ✅ Multi-stage builds\n278: - ✅ Layer caching optimization\n279: - ✅ .dockerignore for minimal context\n280: - ✅ OCI-compliant labels\n281: \n282: ## Documentation\n283: \n284: ### User Documentation\n285: - README.md: Comprehensive user guide\n286: - Quick start examples\n287: - Usage examples\n288: - Troubleshooting guide\n289: - CI/CD integration examples\n290: \n291: ### Developer Documentation\n292: - Build script comments\n293: - Validation script comments\n294: - Inline Dockerfile comments\n295: - Test script documentation\n296: - Makefile help system\n297: \n298: ## Next Steps\n299: \n300: ### Recommended Enhancements\n301: 1. Add security scanning (Trivy/Docker Scout)\n302: 2. Implement SBOM generation\n303: 3. Add image signing (cosign/notary)\n304: 4. Implement image provenance\n305: 5. Add vulnerability reporting\n306: 6. Implement image versioning strategy\n307: \n308: ### Optional Features\n309: 1. Read-only root filesystem\n310: 2. Seccomp profiles\n311: 3. AppArmor profiles\n312: 4. Custom CA certificates\n313: 5. Runtime security policies\n314: \n315: ## Conclusion\n316: \n317: This implementation provides a production-ready, secure, and optimized multi-stage Dockerfile build system for the AgentCube project. All components have been implemented, tested, and documented according to the design specifications.\n318: \n319: The implementation includes:\n320: - ✅ 3-stage multi-stage Dockerfile\n321: - ✅ Build and validation scripts\n322: - ✅ Comprehensive test suite\n323: - ✅ Complete documentation\n324: - ✅ CI/CD integration ready\n325: - ✅ Security best practices\n326: - ✅ Performance optimizations\n327: - ✅ Makefile for convenience\n328: \n329: All files are production-ready and follow Docker best practices.\n\n(End of file - total 329 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032: Dockerfile Multi-Stage Build - Implementation Summary\n\n## Implementation Status\n\n✅ **COMPLETE** - All components implemented and tested\n\n## Overview\n\nThis implementation provides a comprehensive multi-stage Dockerfile build strategy for the AgentCube project, featuring three independent build stages (Builder, Verifier, Runtime) to create optimized production images.\n\n## Files Created\n\n### Core Docker Files\n- **Dockerfile** - Multi-stage Dockerfile with 3 build stages\n- **.dockerignore** - Build context exclusions\n- **requirements.txt** - Python dependencies for picod\n\n### Build Scripts\n- **build.sh** - Single-architecture build script with multiple target support\n- **build-multiarch.sh** - Multi-architecture build script for linux/amd64,linux/arm64","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775883